The paper deals with matrix decomposition and matrix completion, which are common topics in machine learning and data analysis. The use of randomly sampled rows and columns, as well as a subset of observed entries, suggests that the paper may fall under the category of "Large Scale Learning" (cs.LG). The analysis of the relative error bound and sample complexity also suggests that the paper may belong to the categories of "Numerical Analysis" (cs.NA) and "Data Structures and Algorithms" (cs.DS). The use of random sampling and the analysis of the algorithm's performance suggest that the paper may also belong to the categories of "Information Theory" (cs.IT) and "Social and Information Networks" (cs.SI).
